{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/how-to-add-a-custom-background-image-to-any-shopify-theme","result":{"pageContext":{"id":1227,"date":"2021-10-10T06:03:53","date_gmt":"2021-10-10T06:03:53","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=1227"},"modified":"2023-03-27T09:33:08","modified_gmt":"2023-03-27T09:33:08","slug":"how-to-add-a-custom-background-image-to-any-shopify-theme","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/how-to-add-a-custom-background-image-to-any-shopify-theme/","title":{"rendered":"How to add a custom background image to any Shopify theme [Updated 2023]"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Tired of the plain white background of your theme? Having a neat-looking background image on your website can be a bold way to establish your brand: a well thought beautiful image, abstract or not, carries power with it. <br><br>One important thing to understand is that most modern Shopify themes are built on top of sections, therefore adding a background image to the website itself would unlikely yield any results. <br><br>As an example, imagine you&#8217;re placing lego blocks on top of an orange lego wall. Although the wall is orange, the other lego pieces will be on top of it so you won&#8217;t be able to say see that it is orange. In this analogy, the wall is your &lt;body> tag and the other pieces are the Shopify sections. <br><br>Therefore, in this tutorial we&#8217;ll cover how you can add an image to both the website (the orange lego wall) and how you can add an image to each individual section (the lego pieces). At the end we&#8217;ll also take a look into optimizing your image&#8217;s performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-upload-the-image-to-your-website\">Upload the image to your website</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first, let&#8217;s upload the image that will be shown on your website. To do this is, we&#8217;ll use the Shopify store&#8217;s file storage.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>From your admin page, navigate to <strong>Content > Files</strong>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1263\" height=\"693\" class=\"wp-image-2733\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_33.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_33.jpg 1263w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_33-850x466.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_33-1200x658.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_33-768x421.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1263px) 100vw, 1263px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>On the top right, click on <strong>Upload Files</strong> and upload the image you&#8217;d like to use as a background. In this case, we&#8217;ll use this forest image.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1605\" height=\"775\" class=\"wp-image-2735\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_34.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_34.jpg 1605w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_34-850x410.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_34-1200x579.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_34-768x371.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_34-1536x742.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1605px) 100vw, 1605px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Please keep the link of the image you&#8217;ll want to use accessible. You may want to leave this tab open or save the link somewhere.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1567\" height=\"543\" class=\"wp-image-2737\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_36.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_36.jpg 1567w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_36-850x295.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_36-1200x416.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_36-768x266.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_36-1536x532.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1567px) 100vw, 1567px\" /><br></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-adding-the-image-to-the-website-s-body\">Adding the image to the website&#8217;s body</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Firstly let&#8217;s add the image to the website&#8217;s body, which would be the equivalent to the orange lego wall in our previous analogy. If you&#8217;d like to add the image only to a specific section instead please skip to the next part.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>From your Shopify admin, navigate to <strong><strong>online store > themes > actions > edit code</strong></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click on <strong>Add a new snippet</strong> and create a snippet named exactly:<br><br><strong>ezfy-background-image</strong><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1476\" height=\"757\" class=\"wp-image-2741\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_37.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_37.jpg 1476w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_37-850x436.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_37-1200x615.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_37-768x394.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1476px) 100vw, 1476px\" /></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the following code inside this newly created file:<br><br>[gist]0be85df08819873e6dd8f3a02ce17005[gist]<br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replace the text that says &#8220;replaceme.jpg&#8221; with the image URL that you copied beforehand. Make sure it is also between quotes.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1294\" height=\"640\" class=\"wp-image-2758\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_46.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_46.jpg 1294w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_46-850x420.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_46-1200x594.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_46-768x380.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1294px) 100vw, 1294px\" /><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1315\" height=\"544\" class=\"wp-image-2760\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_47.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_47.jpg 1315w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_47-850x352.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_47-1200x496.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_47-768x318.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1315px) 100vw, 1315px\" /></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The following code will add the background image to the body plus all sections except the header, announcement bar and the footer. This is how it looks like on the Dawn theme:<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1541\" height=\"919\" class=\"wp-image-2750\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_38.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_38.jpg 1541w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_38-850x507.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_38-1200x716.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_38-768x458.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_38-1536x916.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1541px) 100vw, 1541px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-adding-the-image-to-individual-sections\">Adding the image to individual sections</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;d like to add a custom background to only a few sections or if you&#8217;re having trouble with the previous code, this may be a viable solution:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>From the <strong>edit code</strong> page, on the top left, click on the three dots and <strong>Customize</strong>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1241\" height=\"642\" class=\"wp-image-2752\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_42.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_42.jpg 1241w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_42-850x440.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_42-1200x621.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_42-768x397.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1241px) 100vw, 1241px\" /></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose the section you&#8217;d like to add a background to. In this case, I&#8217;ll be adding a custom background to our <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/collections-tabs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">copy/paste Collections Tabs section</a>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1537\" height=\"775\" class=\"wp-image-2754\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_43.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_43.jpg 1537w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_43-850x429.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_43-1200x605.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_43-768x387.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1537px) 100vw, 1537px\" /></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Scroll all the way down until you find <strong>&#8220;Custom CSS&#8221;</strong>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the following code. Remember to replace the &#8220;replaceme.jpg&#8221; with your image&#8217;s URL:<br><br><code>> * { background: url(\"replaceme.jpg\") !important; }</code><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>You should see the changes immediately. I think we can all agree this is not the most elegant choice of background for this specific section but, hey, it works!<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1816\" height=\"923\" class=\"wp-image-2756\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_45.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_45.jpg 1816w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_45-850x432.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_45-1200x610.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_45-768x390.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screenshot_45-1536x781.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1816px) 100vw, 1816px\" /></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-final-thoughts\">Final thoughts</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial I used a JPG image that&#8217;s 1.78mb. For the sake of learning this is fine, but in a real world store you don&#8217;t want to use images that large, especially as a background image. <br><br>I would recommend an image that is at most 500kb, also make sure you use <strong>.webp</strong> instead of .jpg. WEBP performs much better. <br><br>If you&#8217;re working alongside a developer you may also want to look into developing a custom choice for your theme where you can implement lazyloading, add a custom field to quickly upload images at the customize page and some other additional functionalities to easily A/B test what works the best for your business. </p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn how you can add a custom background image to your website&#8217;s pages.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1240,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[206],"image_alt":"","featured_image_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/dawn_center-2-850x478.png","featured_image_small_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/dawn_center-2-200x200.png","featured_image_large_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/dawn_center-2-1200x675.png","categories_names":["Blog"],"acf":[],"tag_names":["all themes"],"featured_image_url":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/dawn_center-2.png","featured_image_url_alt":"","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/1227"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/comments?post=1227"}],"version-history":[{"count":10,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/1227/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2766,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/1227/revisions/2766"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media/1240"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media?parent=1227"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/categories?post=1227"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/tags?post=1227"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["330429198","3356652627"]}